summary: This is an email chain from August 2021 regarding the Ghislaine Maxwell case, involving Assistant U.S. Attorneys and staff. The emails discuss forwarding documents for witness folders and scheduling a potential meeting, indicating ongoing case preparation.

events.title: Potential August meeting discussed
events.description: A meeting in August is discussed as a possibility, contingent on a determination based on received items.

locations: One Saint Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: The document is an email chain from August 2021 related to the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case.
It shows Assistant U.S. Attorneys from the Southern District of New York coordinating document handling for witness folders.
The correspondence indicates active case preparation, including scheduling considerations for a potential meeting.
The email signatures confirm the involvement of the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
